# New demo import workflow

When adding a project (e.g. `git subtree` from another repo):

1. Start from up-to-date `main`: `git checkout main && git pull origin main`
2. Create a branch: `git checkout -b add/<FolderName>` (match the root folder name, e.g. `add/ScrollViewDemo`)
3. Add the project (subtree or copy), update the root [README.md](README.md) table
4. Commit with a clear message, e.g. `Add <FolderName> demo`
5. Push: `git push -u origin add/<FolderName>`
6. Open a PR into `main` with a **short** description (these are demos): what the app demonstrates, folder path, optional link to the original repo

Use [GitHub CLI](https://cli.github.com/) when available:

`gh pr create --base main --title "Add <FolderName> demo" --body "$(printf '%s\n' '### Demo' '**Folder:** `FolderName/`' '**What it shows:** …' '' '### Source' '- Repo: …')"`

Adjust the body to 2–4 lines; no long write-ups unless the user asks.
